goals.question: What is the correlation between field u and field v?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of u vs v
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the relationship between the two fields and if there is any correlation between them.

goals.question: What is the distribution of field u?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of values in field u and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of field v?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of values in field v and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the joint distribution of field u and field v?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the joint distribution of the two fields and if there are any patterns or clusters.

goals.question: What is the average value of field u?
goals.rationale: This question does not require a visualization and can be answered by calculating the mean of field u.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between field u and field v?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Field u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of field u?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['v'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['v'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('v')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of field v?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=50, cmap=plt.cm.Blues)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the joint distribution of field u and field v?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.axvline(x=data['u'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the average value of field u?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
